2019-12-20 11:47:00	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> no
2019-12-20 11:47:13	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> why not?
2019-12-20 11:47:36	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> because a set is a list of unordered values
2019-12-20 11:47:49	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> just because the current implementation is ordered, you shouldn't reply upon that
2019-12-20 11:48:41	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> as if the implementation changes to not use Hash your stuff would break
2019-12-20 11:48:55	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> would be better to always assume a Set is unordered
2019-12-20 11:49:08	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> there are no plans to do that, however
2019-12-20 11:49:46	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> no, but still better than having code based on false assumptions
2019-12-20 11:50:37	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> that could change in the future, which would most likely be hard to fix
2019-12-20 11:51:07	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> no, it wouldn't be hard to fix. You could just switch to `Hash(T, nil)`
2019-12-20 11:51:35	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> the current `Set` implementation is not terribly complex
2019-12-20 11:51:53	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> so just do that from the beginning and avoid having to fix anything in the first place if insertion order is needed
2019-12-20 11:52:29	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> i just dont like the idea of relying on the private implementation of something that can be changed at anytime, breaking the code
2019-12-20 11:52:30	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> worrying about things that have a small likelihood of changing in the future is a distraction
